              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- About This Work -->
    <section class="py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-white border-b border-gray-200">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-playfair">About This Work</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-700 space-y-4">
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed">
            What remains when we strip away the illusions we hold about ourselves?
          </p>
          <p>
            <em>The Contradicted Existence</em> examines this question through twenty-four essays that refuse to comfort or prescribe. This work explores fundamental contradictions: we are selfish yet unified with existence, determined yet experiencing free will, capable of both good and evil, isolated yet desperate for belonging.
          </p>
          <p>
            The first section confronts selfishness directly—not whether we should be selfish, but acknowledging that we are, distinguishing between natural selfishness (conscious acceptance) and pathological selfishness (narcissistic denial).
          </p>
          <p>
            Death appears not as something to overcome but as motivator. Sexual instinct is revealed as directing far more of our actions than we consciously acknowledge. Gender dynamics receive frank examination presenting complementary rather than identical roles—a perspective many readers will find controversial.
          </p>
          <p>
            Consciousness and free will are explored through paradox: we experience free will within deterministic existence. The self we think we are—constructed from family labels, school grades, job titles, others' opinions—is revealed as image, not essence.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
            This is not transformation literature. This is philosophical inquiry examining what is, not what we wish to be.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Complete Chapter List -->
    <section class="py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-50 to-white">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 font-playfair">Complete Chapter List</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600">24 philosophical essays examining the contradictions of existence</p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          {[
            "You Are Selfish",
            "You Are What You Do",
            "You Are What You Love",
            "You Want to Be Loved",
            "We Fear Death",
            "We Are Self-Destructive",
            "Sexual Instinct Directs Our Actions",
            "The Interdependence of Men and Women",
            "The Unity of Existence",
            "Existence is Contradicted",
            "You Are Not the Center of the Universe",
            "Free Will is Predestined",
            "We Need a Belief System",
            "Society Has a Massive Impact on You",
            "Religious and Scientific Ideologies",
            "The State Doesn't Exist",
            "Heaven and Hell are Mental States",
            "We Are All Capable of Good and Evil",
            "The Need for Deep Sense of Belonging",
            "Who You Are",
            "Your Consciousness",
            "You Can't Always Get What You Want",
            "Courage, Love, and Humility: Pillars of Power",
            "Everything Happens at the Right Time"
          ].map((chapter, index) => (
            <div class="group bg-white hover:bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-slate-200 hover:border-blue-300 hover:shadow-md transition-all duration-200">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500 to-blue-600 text-white rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">
                  {index + 1}
                </span>
                <p class="text-gray-800 font-medium text-sm leading-snug pt-1 group-hover:text-blue-700 transition-colors">{chapter}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
